        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-05-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-05-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="356" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d356">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/5–1149: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-11">May 11,
                            1949</date>.<lb/>[Received May 11—1:18 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>996. Nanking <hi rend="italic">Hsin Hua Jih Pao</hi> May 10 carries exclusive
                    announcement of formation of new Nanking municipal government. Chinese People’s
                    Revolutionary Military Council appointed Liu Po-cheng as Mayor, Ko Ching-shih
                    and Chang Lin-chih as Deputy Mayors.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 996; repeated Shanghai 554, Peiping 153, Embassy Canton 396.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
